  "decision_conditions": [
    "The development to which this permission relates must be begun no later than three years from the date of this decision notice. \r\rReason: To comply with the provision of Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990. \r",
    "The development hereby permitted shall be carried out in complete accordance with the approved plans and drawings listed in this decision notice, other than where those details are altered pursuant to conditions of this planning permission. \r\rReason: For the avoidance of doubt and in the interests of proper planning. \r",
    "All new external work and finishes and work of making good shall match the original work in respect of the materials, colour, texture, profile and finished appearance, except where indicated otherwise on the drawings hereby approved or unless otherwise required by condition.\r\rReason: To preserve the character and appearance of the host building and the local area. (Policies Q5, Q8 and Q11 of the Lambeth Local Plan (2021)).\r",
    "Prior to the commencement of the development hereby permitted, drawings of all external construction detail for the proposed extension works along with details of the solar panels, including sections at a scale of 1:10 shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. \r\rReason: In order to safeguard the architectural integrity of the host building and wider street scene. (Policies Q5, Q8 and Q11 of the Lambeth Local Plan (2021)). \r",
    "Prior to the commencement of development hereby permitted, a full schedule and details of the materials to be used in the external elevations (including RAL numbers where appropriate) shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. This shall include the opportunity to view a sample panel which is to be provided on site. The development hereby permitted shall be thereafter built in accordance with the approved details.\r\rReason: In order to safeguard the architectural integrity of the host building and wider street scene. (Policies Q5, Q8 and Q11 of the Lambeth Local Plan (2021)).\r"
  ],
